5:
...What do you mean Silkhare has
been "canceled"?
9:
Well, she's been making a bit of a
stir in the Palpebran tabloids...
14:
Ngh... I just don't get it! All I wanted
were some friends! Is that such a
crime?!
18:
You've good intentions, but you're
going about it all wrong.
22: Then what am I supposed to do?!
26:
If you're such experts, why don't you
tell me, hm? Teach me how to make
friends. Right this instant!
30:
Perhaps if you were to act normal
for once, you may actually make a
few.
34:
If you don't give me some REAL
advice, I'll pluck those ears right off
of your head...
39:
Friendship isn't something you can
force. 'Sides, who needs friends that
don't actually wanna be around you?
49:
I'm going to make a hundred friends
and found a new idol group—FRD100.
52:
Up until now, I never believed it was
possible. But I've begun to think that
maybe—just maybe—I can do it.
58:
Then let's achieve your dream.
Together.
63: Stella! You mean you'll help me?
68:
If it is friends you desire, friends you
shall have! I, too, shall lend you my
strength!
78:
Needs change with the times. And
these times call for a MUSICAL!
82:
A wonderful singing voice? Stunning
acrobatics? You are EXACTLY the
person I have been looking for!
92:
I see... So you want me for your
production? I must say, you have an
eye for talent!
97: Oooh, a musical sounds like a blast!
102:
...Working with those other BRASS
hacks is an irksome thought, but
one I can tolerate.
105:
However, unfortunately for you, I do
not intend to stand on another
person's stage.
108:
At long last, I have my own dream to
chase. I can't waste my time on—
116:
I have already given you my word—
I shall help make your dream come
true.
120:
Be part of my musical, and you shall
make TONS of friends!
128:
You shall indeed! In fact, you
already have! You and I are friends
now.
137:
Fine, fox. I'll take part in your little
musical. Your whole world will know
the glory of Queen Silkhare!
144: Oh, this just won't do at all!
148:
What's wrong? Rehearsal isn't going
well for you?
152:
Don't be a fool, boy. Rehearsal is
smooth as can be. What do you
take me for, an amateur?
157:
Ah... This must be about making
friends, then.
161:
I still haven't the faintest idea what
to do to make friends!
164:
At this rate, I'll never be able to form
FRD100...
172:
Hey, Silky! Got a sec? I found this
super cute café the other day.
Wanna check it out with me
sometime?
174:
I suppose I wouldn't mind... I'll pencil
you in when you've decided on a
date.
178:
Silkhare, Silkhare! Look! I found a
cool leaf! You can have it.
185:
*sigh* I just don't understand. 
How does one go about making 
friends, anyway?
191:
Silkhare! Seriously?! You're getting
along with lots of people already!
196:
I am?!
Er, I mean... Of course I am!
199:
But... None of them have called me
their "friend" yet.
208:
That's okay. We're all your friends
already.
223:
DANG IT, SILKHAAAAARE!
You ate my cake! 
I was saving that for later!
228:
WHAT? Don't you DARE criticize me,
you greedy little rat! It's only fair,
after you ate my pudding!
234:
Cowdy there, Silkhare! I'd be over
the moon if you'd give me your
autograph...
239:
Wow... It was a rough start, but it
sounds like she's even starting to
get along with the BRASS folks.
243:
It's all thanks to you. She is finally
able to make friends because you
were there for her.
246:
You did what I never could. Though
I've been by her side all this time, 
I couldn't help her. 
I couldn't even be her friend...
251:
What? No way you believe that.
That's a load of crap.
256:
Nimbus is right, you know. I'm sure
she's always seen you as a friend.
263:
It's time. Places, everyone!
Rabby, are you ready?
270:
I'm sorry to bring this up at a time
like this, but... Do you see me as... 
A friend?
274:
Huh? What a stupid question.
Of course not.
277:
You're more than that—you're
family.
Isn't it obvious?
281:
Indeed... That's what we were all
along.
285:
Oh, it's starting!
Come on, Rabby! It's showtime!
289:
Ladiiies and gentlemeeen!
Welcome, one and all!
Are you ready to bow before the
great Queen Silkhare?
